external_knowledge:
- "shining star" refers to the player with the highest performance;
- "outshines others" refers to having the highest average points;
- "earning the highest average points per tournament" means the player has the best average points across all tournaments.

- "Top 3 players" refers to players ranked 1st, 2nd, and 3rd in their region based on total points;
- "Total points" and "average placement" are metrics used to evaluate player performance;
- "Region ID" and "location ID" are identifiers linking players and tournaments to their respective geographical areas.

sql:
SELECT player_name
FROM players
WHERE rank = (SELECT MIN(rank) FROM players);

SELECT type_name, description
FROM tournament_types
WHERE type_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Shining stars' refers to players who have performed exceptionally well;
- 'Top 3 most lucrative tournaments' refers to the tournaments with the highest prize money;
- 'Region' refers to the geographical area from which the players hail;
- 'Outshone their peers' means the players have earned more points than the average points earned by players from their region.

- "shone brightest" refers to the player's best performance in a tournament;
- "radiance against the average glow" refers to the difference between the player's total points in their best performance and the average points earned by players from the same region in the same tournament;
- "greatest surge in performance" refers to the largest positive difference between the player's best performance and the regional average.

sql:
